```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "queue": "largemem",
      "allocation": "quinnlab",
      "walltime": "01:00:00",
      "tasks": 1
    },
    "software_modules": [
      "gcc/7.1.0",
      "openmpi/3.1.4",
      "R/3.5.3"
    ],
    "script": "TNFileJoining_Hill05.R",
    "arguments": [
      "/scratch/js4yd/MorrisSA/TNprocessing/",
      "DateColumnNames.txt",
      "SAResults_HillStreamflow_p6_t.txt",
      "/scratch/js4yd/MorrisSA/TNprocessing/TNdata/",
      "TNSAreps_Hill05_All.RData",
      "SAResults_HillTN05_p3_All.txt"
    ]
  }
}
```

This JSON object describes the application running the script as Slurm, a workload manager used for high-performance computing. It also details the resource requirements specified in the script using `#SBATCH` directives, including the queue, allocation, walltime, and number of tasks. The software modules loaded before running the script are also listed, along with the R script and its arguments.
